。这位歌手在社交媒体上<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kelly-clarkson-addresses-allegations-of-toxic-work-environment-on-her-talk-show-3443616">发帖回应了这些报道</a>：“我爱我在<em>凯利·克拉克森秀</em>上的团队，发现任何人在这个节目中感到被忽视或不受尊重是不可接受的。”</p><p>与此同时，泰勒·斯威夫特 (Taylor Swift) 和特拉维斯·凯尔斯 (Travis Kelce) <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/taylor-swift-makes-surprise-appearance-on-snl-season-premiere-3515101">上周在《周六夜现场》(SNL) 节目中出人意料地</a>亮相，引起了人们的关注。凯尔斯出现在 NFL 的小品中，同样开玩笑说他们的关系接管了体育板块，而斯威夫特则介绍了音乐嘉宾<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ice-spice">Ice Spice</a> 。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kelly-clarkson-denies-taylor-swift-and-travis-kelce-relationship-diss-3519058">凯莉·克拉克森否认泰勒·斯威夫特和特拉维斯·凯尔斯关系的</a>帖子首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
利-安妮·平诺克 (Leigh-Anne Pinnock) 讲述了遭受种族主义的经历：“为什么我感觉自己被忽视了？” https://www.nme.com/news/music/leigh-anne-pinnock-opens-up-about-suffering-racism-why-do-i-feel-invisible-3519060?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=leigh-安妮·平诺克公开谈论遭受种族主义的痛苦，为什么我感觉自己看不见Max PilleySun, 22 Oct 2023 10:10:33 +0000 Music NewsNewsPop https://www.nme.com/?p=3519060 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="利-安妮·平诺克" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “我内心深处意识到我就是问题所在，这让我失去了信心。”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/leigh-anne-pinnock-opens-up-about-suffering-racism-why-do-i-feel-invisible-3519060">莉·安妮·平诺克 (Leigh-Anne Pinnock) 的帖子讲述了遭受种族主义的痛苦：“为什么我感觉自己被忽视了？”</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="利-安妮·平诺克" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/leighanne_pinnock-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/leigh-anne">Leigh-Anne Pinnock</a>公开讲述了自 2011 年凭借<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/little-mix">《Little Mix》</a>成名以来她所面临的种族歧视。</p><p>她与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/perrie-edwards">佩里·爱德华兹 (Perrie Edwards)</a> 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jesy-nelson">杰西·尼尔森 (Jesy Nelson</a> ) 和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jade-thirlwall">杰德·瑟尔沃尔 (Jade Thirlwall)</a>组成的组合当年赢得了<em>《X Factor》</em> ，这是唯一一个赢得真人秀节目冠军的女子组合。他们的五首单曲在英国排名第一，全球唱片销量达 7500 万张，播放量超过 150 亿次。</p><p>然而，平诺克在接受 <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/oct/21/leigh-anne-pinnock-little-mix-interview"><i>《卫报》</i></a>采访时解释说，尽管取得了如此成功，但与她的乐队成员相比，她一直在为自己受到的对待方式而挣扎。</p><p> “我总是说，‘实现了我的梦想，我应该有这样的感觉吗？’”她说。 “为什么有时我觉得我还不如不在这里呢？为什么我感觉自己没有被注意到？为什么我感觉自己看不见？为什么我不像其他人那样受到重视？只是感觉不太对劲。”</p><p> “我内心深处意识到我就是问题所在，这让我失去了信心。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Leigh-Anne：“不要说爱”[官方视频]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/hNSJWpULrJA?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>她接着解释说，当 Little Mix 在巴西演出时，一个清晰的时刻出现了，主要是黑人观众开始专门为她欢呼。 “我一直都知道我正在接触黑人女性，但我没有看到她们。他们没有参加演出或粉丝活动。”</p><p> “巴西在帮助我理解我被低估和被忽视的一切感受方面发挥了巨大作用。它证实了我的感受。但这并没有消除痛苦，因为它一直在发生。我回到英国后仍然有这种感觉。”</p><p>平诺克与作家娜塔莉·莫里斯合作撰写的回忆录<em>《相信</em>》将于 10 月 26 日出版。</p><p> The singer first publicly discussed the issue of racism when she made the BBC documentary <em>Leigh-Anne: Race, Pop and Power</em> . In it, Pinnock, whose parents are both mixed-race, discusses with peers including <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sugababes">Sugababes</a> &#39; Keisha Buchanan, whether being a light-skinned Black woman made her a more “palatable” option for powerful music executives.</p><p> Reflecting on that discussion, Pinnock told <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/oct/21/leigh-anne-pinnock-little-mix-interview"><i>The Guardian</i></a> , “I know I&#39;m helping some people, and I know I&#39;m doing a good thing, and I&#39;m going to continue to do that. And one thing I&#39;m 100% going to do is talk about light-skinned privilege. I truly believe it&#39;s helped me to get to where I am today.”</p><p> Nelson left Little Mix in 2020 and the group went on indefinite hiatus in 2022. In June this year, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-leigh-anne-pinnock-first-ever-solo-single-dont-say-love-music-video-little-mix-3456937">Pinnock released her debut solo single &#39;Don&#39;t Say Love&#39;</a> under the name Leigh-Anne, a garage and house-inspired track produced by Jon Bellion and Pete Nappi.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/leigh-anne-pinnock-hints-debut-album-will-be-released-next-year-3498949">She also recently hinted that her debut solo album might be out as early as next year</a> . “[It&#39;s] coming together quicker than I think anyone thought, which is good. I reckon next year for sure. Because I want to tour like I want to perform, I belong on stage.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/leigh-anne-pinnock-opens-up-about-suffering-racism-why-do-i-feel-invisible-3519060">Leigh-Anne Pinnock opens up about suffering racism: “Why do I feel invisible?”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
